## Shellwise Improvement Plan \'97 Making It Viral-Worthy\
\
### Root Cause Analysis: Why Shellwise Falls Short\
\
After studying TermCoach's source code and testing both tools, here are the **critical gaps**:\
\
| Area | TermCoach (tc) | Shellwise (sw) | Impact |\
|------|---------------|----------------|--------|\
| **Interactive loop** | `while(!explicitExit)` with readline restore on close | Simple `while True` with `input()` \'97 drops on readline close | **tc stays open, sw exits** |\
| **Command routing** | `which` check \uc0\u8594  direct exec; fallback to AI | Heuristic `is_natural_language()` \'97 fragile | **sw misclassifies "list files" as shell cmd** |\
| **TUI detection** | Dedicated `tui.ts` \'97 exits tc for vim/nano/top | `ls` wrongly classified as interactive | **sw exits on `ls` from AI** |\
| **Safety** | Local classifier (READ/WRITE/CATASTROPHIC) + hard blocker | Trusts AI classification entirely | **tc blocks `rm -rf /` even if AI suggests it** |\
| **Execution** | `spawn` with arg arrays + shell syntax detection | `subprocess.Popen(shell=True)` | **tc safer, sw vulnerable to injection** |\
| **Context** | cwd listing, git branch/dirty, pkg manager, history | OS, arch, distro, cwd only | **tc gives AI much richer context** |\
| **Error handling** | Try/catch per input \uc0\u8594  prompt stays alive | Minimal \'97 crashes propagate | **tc survives AI failures** |\
| **Caching** | JSONL cache with TTL, hit counting, refresh on fail | None | **tc faster, sw repeats AI calls** |\
| **Config** | `~/.shellwise/config.json` + Zod validation + dotenv | None | **tc configurable, sw hardcoded** |\
| **Model reliability** | Model rotation on 429, retry on transient, Zod validation | Single model, no retry, fragile JSON parse | **tc more resilient** |\
| **UI/UX** | Colorful banner, git-aware prompt, proper spinner | Basic banner, static prompt, no spinner | **tc looks polished** |\
| **Tests** | 35+ unit + integration tests | 67 tests but missing core/model coverage | Both decent, tc more integration-focused |\
