### Phase 1: Critical Fixes (Must-Have for Usability)\
\
#### 1.1 Fix Interactive Mode \'97 Never Exit Unexpectedly\
**Files:** `shellwise/__main__.py`, `shellwise/core.py`\
- Wrap interactive loop in outer `while True` that restores readline on unexpected close\
- Add try/except around each input processing \'97 errors show message, return to prompt\
- Only exit on explicit commands (`exit`, `quit`, `bye`, `q`, `Ctrl+D`)\
- **Reference:** `TermCoach/src/modes/interactive.ts` lines 165-336\
\
#### 1.2 Fix Command Routing \'97 Direct Commands vs AI Fallback\
**Files:** `shellwise/ai.py`, `shellwise/core.py`\
- Replace fragile `is_natural_language()` heuristic with `which`-based detection\
- If first token is a valid command \uc0\u8594  execute directly (streaming output)\
- If command not found \uc0\u8594  fall back to AI translation\
- Support `ai <text>` prefix to force AI mode\
- **Reference:** `TermCoach/src/shell/known-commands.ts`\
\
#### 1.3 Fix TUI Detection \'97 Don't Exit on `ls`\
**Files:** `shellwise/ai.py`\
- Create dedicated `INTERACTIVE_TUI_CMDS` set (vim, nano, top, htop, less, man, ssh, tmux, etc.)\
- Only prompt to exit sw mode for actual TUI commands\
- `ls`, `du`, `find`, `grep` etc. should execute and show output inside sw mode\
- **Reference:** `TermCoach/src/core/tui.ts`\
\
#### 1.4 Add Local Safety Classifier\
**Files:** New `shellwise/classifier.py`\
- Local READ/WRITE/CRITICAL classification independent of AI\
- Hard-block catastrophic patterns (`rm -rf /`, `dd if=...of=/dev/sdX`, fork bombs)\
- Re-classify AI-suggested commands locally before execution\
- **Reference:** `TermCoach/src/core/classifier.ts`, `TermCoach/src/core/safety.ts`\
\
#### 1.5 Fix `sw "query"` One-Shot Mode\
**Files:** `shellwise/__main__.py`\
- One-shot mode should execute and return to shell prompt (current behavior is correct)\
- But add proper error handling \'97 don't crash on AI failure\
- Show friendly error message and exit with code 1\
\
